{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_011Zh4VGTS93nftHU37yVBut","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Here's the full contents of the auth routes test file:\n\n## Test Setup Pattern Summary\n\nThe test file demonstrates a comprehensive vitest setup pattern for testing Hono routes with PostgreSQL integration:\n\n**Key aspects:**\n\n1. **Vitest Structure** (lines 5-30)\n   - Uses standard vitest hooks: `describe`, `it`, `beforeAll`, `afterAll`, `beforeEach`, `expect`\n   - Declares shared state in the describe scope: `rawSql`, `authDb`, `app`, `stubDb`\n\n2. **Database Setup** (lines 38-62, 69-70)\n   - `beforeAll`: Creates PostgreSQL connection via `postgres` package and initializes schema (auth_challenges, refresh_tokens tables)\n   - `afterAll`: Closes the connection with `rawSql.end()`\n   - `beforeEach`: Truncates tables with `TRUNCATE ... RESTART IDENTITY` to ensure clean state between tests\n\n3. **Route Configuration** (lines 71-84)\n   - Creates a fresh Hono app instance for each test\n   - Routes auth handlers with: `authDb`, stubbed `db` object, JWT secret, cluster, and TTL config\n\n4. **Test Data & Utilities** (lines 36, 135-137)\n   - Uses Solana's `Keypair.generate()` for test wallets\n   - TweetNaCl for message signing (detached signatures)\n   - Base58 encoding for signatures\n   - JWT verification using `jwtVerify` from jose\n\n5. **Database Constants** (lines 20-21)\n   - DATABASE_URL from environment or localhost default\n   - Test JWT secret encoded as bytes\n\nThe pattern is comprehensive: multi-table setup, full auth flow testing (challenge → verify → refresh → logout), edge cases (wrong wallet, wrong signature, nonce reuse), and token rotation validation.\n\nFile path: `/workspaces/rng-utopia/backend/services/backend/src/__tests__/auth-routes.test.ts`"}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"cd479181-9c0f-4c58-8b77-ba63a57dd2e1","uuid":"b9d94dfd-73ca-47df-8c18-307d2d0da431","timestamp":"2